text: Earl is an unincorporated community in Callaway County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Earl was established in 1891, and remained in operation until 1907. The community was named after Earl Sexton, the son of a local merchant. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Callaway County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Earl, Missouri
